  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "They were using these traitors to the Jews for their benefit.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "They had no respect for them.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "They respect Netanyahu a lot more, although they don't like him, than they ever, ever could have respected a traitor to their own people.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "Because the Arabs have-- have-- also have their own dignity and their own honor.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "And they know a traitor, and disrespect him.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "And this is-- and I'm very happy that recently that there was a change in government and the Marxist atheists were thrown out.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "And now we have a chance again.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "Had it not been so, Israel could have been destroyed.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 43,
      "text": "The Jews in Israel would have had to be evacuated within the next 10 years.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 44,
      "text": "And there would have been an Arab, an Arab-Judeo state.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 45,
      "text": "Some Jews would have remained.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 46,
      "text": "Some of the [? yeshivas ?] would have remained still.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 47,
      "text": "There's contribution from foreign countries, but they would have been in the subservient positions to Arabs, as Jews have been traditional to Arabs.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 48,
      "text": "We have lived with Arabs.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 49,
      "text": "We have lived with Arabs since the destruction of the first temple 500 BC until now.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 50,
      "text": "The Jews were-- when we were in Persia and in Iran, and Iraq, and Syria, we have lived with Arabs for 2,500 years.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 51,
      "text": "So we can live with Arabs.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 52,
      "text": "But we couldn't live under Marxist atheism, which talks about the pro-Zionist period, and was wanting the destruction of the Jewish religion, and the Jewish people.",
      "word_count": 26
    }
  ],
